269
00:22:40,877 --> 00:22:43,846
- Thank you, sir. - Thanks for your hard work.

270
00:22:43,846 --> 00:22:44,977
I'll be off, then.

271
00:22:58,187 --> 00:22:59,756
I don't want to see you wasting your talent.

272
00:23:00,296 --> 00:23:02,996
I asked to see you because I wanted to have a talk with you.

273
00:23:04,026 --> 00:23:05,026
I see.

274
00:23:05,026 --> 00:23:08,397
I know you haven't been preparing to apply for art schools,

275
00:23:08,566 --> 00:23:09,836
but you're in 11th grade now,

276
00:23:09,836 --> 00:23:12,766
so I think you'll get in with just a little bit of effort.

277
00:23:13,637 --> 00:23:15,877
Thank you for thinking so highly of me.

278
00:23:17,177 --> 00:23:19,776
Hye Mi, I'll help you.

279
00:23:20,246 --> 00:23:22,177
You should tell your parents.

280
00:23:22,576 --> 00:23:25,086
Shall I speak with your parents in person?

281
00:23:29,117 --> 00:23:30,157
Sure.

282
00:23:45,437 --> 00:23:46,506
Eat up.

283
00:23:47,536 --> 00:23:48,836
Thanks for the food.

284
00:24:10,566 --> 00:24:13,066
Is there something you want to say to me?

285
00:24:16,766 --> 00:24:17,836
No.

286
00:24:23,336 --> 00:24:25,006
- Here you go. - Thanks.

287
00:26:01,506 --> 00:26:03,947
Hey, I told you to come quickly. You little...

288
00:26:04,846 --> 00:26:05,977
Get in.

289
00:26:08,516 --> 00:26:09,917
Why are you so late?

290
00:26:10,316 --> 00:26:11,546
Darn it.

291
00:26:56,256 --> 00:26:57,566
(An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.)

292
00:26:57,566 --> 00:26:58,897
(You'll suffer the same!)

293
00:27:02,197 --> 00:27:04,266
(Funeral Arrangements and Data on the Late Mun Song Myeon)

294
00:27:16,117 --> 00:27:18,917
We all remember the vigorous speech of this man...

295
00:27:18,917 --> 00:27:20,556
from 30 years ago.

296
00:27:20,556 --> 00:27:23,856
The ideal society I have in mind is people living in unity,

297
00:27:23,856 --> 00:27:26,356
and where everyone doesn't worry about food, clothing,

298
00:27:26,356 --> 00:27:27,996
and other things like that.

299
00:27:27,996 --> 00:27:29,996
Where people don't commit dirty acts,

300
00:27:29,996 --> 00:27:33,566
and a world where everyone can live their daily lives happily.

301
00:27:33,737 --> 00:27:37,237
To him, there was a heartbreaking death of one man.

302
00:27:37,367 --> 00:27:39,737
Last July 2, at Yeoeuido St. Mary's Hospital,

303
00:27:39,737 --> 00:27:43,336
a 15-year-old laborer died of mercury poisoning.

304
00:27:43,707 --> 00:27:47,177
The name of the boy who died at 15 from mercury poisoning...

305
00:27:47,177 --> 00:27:48,816
was Mun Song Myeon.

306
00:27:48,816 --> 00:27:52,286
He always said he wanted to visit his home in the countryside.

307
00:27:52,286 --> 00:27:55,117
That's what lingers in my head the most.

308
00:27:55,117 --> 00:27:56,816
He said he couldn't wait to go home.

309
00:27:57,086 --> 00:27:59,326
Born from parents who farmed in the countryside,

310
00:27:59,326 --> 00:28:01,296
he was the third son out of six siblings,

311
00:28:01,296 --> 00:28:03,996
and he was a sincere and kind child.

312
00:28:04,566 --> 00:28:08,137
The reason he started working at a factory when he was 15...

313
00:28:08,137 --> 00:28:10,197
was because of his high school tuition.

314
00:28:10,197 --> 00:28:12,867
It was a company that made mercury thermometers.

315
00:28:12,867 --> 00:28:14,707
When he was working,

316
00:28:14,707 --> 00:28:18,147
he didn't have any idea that something was wrong.

317
00:28:18,147 --> 00:28:19,947
He was the tallest one.

318
00:28:19,947 --> 00:28:22,746
He was taller and healthier than friends his age,

319
00:28:22,746 --> 00:28:24,987
and about a month after he started working at the factory,

320
00:28:24,987 --> 00:28:27,786
he started to suffer from an unknown pain.

321
00:28:27,786 --> 00:28:29,457
What's wrong? Are you sick?

322
00:28:29,457 --> 00:28:32,187
- My back hurts, and I can't sleep. - Your back?

323
00:28:32,187 --> 00:28:34,996
The university hospital couldn't identify his disease,

324
00:28:34,996 --> 00:28:37,566
and his body felt numb and sore.

325
00:28:37,566 --> 00:28:40,397
He couldn't even eat properly. The pain was so severe...

326
00:28:40,397 --> 00:28:43,637
that even his teeth started shaking and falling out.

327
00:28:43,637 --> 00:28:46,167
After being hospitalized for two months,

328
00:28:46,167 --> 00:28:48,377
his disease was identified as mercury poisoning.

329
00:28:48,907 --> 00:28:51,846
The company ordered him to inject mercury inside a closed space...

330
00:28:51,846 --> 00:28:53,647
without any safety equipment.

331
00:28:53,647 --> 00:28:57,016
As a result, he suffered from acute mercury poisoning.

332
00:28:57,746 --> 00:28:58,987
But his company...

333
00:28:58,987 --> 00:29:01,586
refused to accept it as an industrial accident,

334
00:29:01,586 --> 00:29:04,026
claiming it was due to pesticides from the countryside.

335
00:29:04,556 --> 00:29:06,157
After this case was covered by the media,

336
00:29:06,157 --> 00:29:08,526
it was finally accepted as an industrial accident...

337
00:29:08,526 --> 00:29:10,026
(Joint Memorial Service for the late Mun Song Myeon)

338
00:29:10,026 --> 00:29:11,596
(June 30, 2019)

339
00:29:11,596 --> 00:29:13,066
I'd like to thank everyone...

340
00:29:13,066 --> 00:29:15,996
who came here, in remembrance of Song Myeon.

341
00:29:15,996 --> 00:29:18,566
But 12 days after it was accepted as an industrial accident,

342
00:29:18,566 --> 00:29:21,377
he passed away without even leaving a will.

343
00:29:21,377 --> 00:29:24,776
It's already been more than 30 years.

344
00:29:24,776 --> 00:29:26,346
But nothing has changed.

345
00:29:26,346 --> 00:29:29,576
I really hope there won't be a second Song Myeon...

346
00:29:29,576 --> 00:29:32,086
and that no one gets hurt or dies.

347
00:29:32,086 --> 00:29:34,016
That's my biggest wish.

348
00:29:34,016 --> 00:29:37,427
Mun Song Myeon is asking from 30 years ago.

349
00:29:38,227 --> 00:29:40,897
"What has changed?"

350
00:29:40,897 --> 00:29:42,056
(The late Mun Song Myeon)

351
00:29:42,056 --> 00:29:45,167
(Doctor Detective)

352
00:29:45,296 --> 00:29:46,496
Oh, no!

353
00:29:46,496 --> 00:29:47,937
What is that?

354
00:29:47,937 --> 00:29:49,967
Stop! No, please!

355
00:29:49,967 --> 00:29:51,737
Who are you?

356
00:29:51,737 --> 00:29:53,937
Me? A doctor.

357
00:29:53,937 --> 00:29:56,536
If it weren't for you, he could've been hurt badly.

358
00:29:56,536 --> 00:29:59,306
The police want us to investigate?

359
00:29:59,306 --> 00:30:01,417
His girlfriend secretly fed him a pesticide.

360
00:30:01,417 --> 00:30:04,086
Ma'am, I really didn't kill Jin Sung.

361
00:30:04,086 --> 00:30:06,187
Please, you have to believe me!

362
00:30:06,187 --> 00:30:07,556
What am I missing?

363
00:30:07,556 --> 00:30:09,756
Is it an industrial accident or not?

364
00:30:09,756 --> 00:30:11,026
Is it, or is it not?

365
00:30:11,026 --> 00:30:12,026
Mr. Huh.

366
00:30:12,657 --> 00:30:13,996
Let's try that again.

367
00:30:13,996 --> 00:30:15,556
I'll carry it with me...

368
00:30:15,556 --> 00:30:17,397
and take care of it.

369
00:30:17,397 --> 00:30:18,526
Peace.

370
00:30:18,526 --> 00:30:20,127
I was thoughtless.

371
00:30:20,127 --> 00:30:22,737
I won't cause trouble for TL ever again.

372
00:30:22,737 --> 00:30:25,036
Like you asked, I made some changes to UDC.

373
00:30:25,036 --> 00:30:27,177
What have you done to UDC?

374
00:30:27,177 --> 00:30:30,546
Do you know how many innocent people got hurt or died?

375
00:30:30,546 --> 00:30:31,977
One day,

376
00:30:32,346 --> 00:30:34,276
you'll be brought to justice.
